<a name="skipmaincontent"></a><h1 class="bac">Global Commercial Banking and Global Product Solutions MBA Intern Program</h1>
<h2 class="bac">Our Business</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Commercial Banking (GCB) generates more than $10 billion in annual revenue and $4 billion in net income from a variety of market-leading businesses. It serves more than 100,000 business banking and more than 30,000 middle-market clients through dedicated client teams who provide seamless, integrated delivery of the bank’s full capabilities. GCB associates offer clients unrivaled market access, flexibility and value from their banking relationship through our core businesses.
</p>

<p class="bac">
Global Product Solutions (GPS) provides integrated working capital management and treasury solutions to more than 150,000 clients around the world, including small businesses, middle-market and large corporations, multi-nationals, financial institutions and governments. GPS offers services including treasury management, trade finance, foreign exchange, short-term credit, liquidity management, commercial card, merchant services and group banking. Bank of America is the number-one treasury and trade services provider in the United States and a leading provider worldwide. GPS associates serve as financial advisors to clients by combining treasury management expertise with a thorough understanding of each client’s business and industry.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview</h2>
<p class="bac">
The Global Commercial Banking/Global Product Solutions Leadership Program was designed to accomplish two goals - accelerate the growth needed to be successful in a client-facing role and develop future leaders for Our Businesses. The leadership program comprises credit, end-to-end treasury management and client management Training, providing greater exposure across the Global Commercial Banking and Global Product Solutions business groups. Associates in this program develop the skills and experience needed to accelerate their Bank of America career.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications</h2>
<p class="bac">
Leadership program candidates must have a MBA degree plus a minimum of three (3) years client-facing experience with a demonstrated record of achievement. In addition, candidates should have deep and broad finance knowledge, excellent verbal and written communication skills, and strong leadership skills.  
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Candidate Profile:
<ul class="bac">
	<li>MBA or equivalent graduate degree from an accredited college or university</li>
	<li>3-5  years of work experience prior to entering graduate school</li>
	<li>Strong leadership and communication skills</li>
	<li>Previous client-facing experience</li>
	<li>Geographic flexibility</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Internships:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Interns work for 10-12 weeks in challenging roles that mirror the positions of full-time GCB/GPS MBA Leadership program associates. In conjunction with the job responsibilities, interns will participate in GCB/GPS MBA functions including Training sessions, informational lunches, networking events, and community service opportunities.   Interns will also have a formal support structure including a Peer Coach, Assignment Manager and Program Manager.  
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training</h2>
<p class="bac">
The Training component of the leadership program consists of classroom and Web-based courses. Throughout the program, formal Training is combined with on-the-job activities designed to apply knowledge of technical, analytical, sales, and professional skills.  During the program, each associate is provided a support network, consisting of a hiring manager, program manager, peer coach and mentor who provide guidance and coaching.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Locations</h2>
<p class="bac">
Positions are available in major markets across the Bank of America footprint. Line of business and location assignment is based on business need and candidate interest. Geographic flexibility is required at the end of the program in an effort to fill business critical roles across our footprint.
</p>


<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

